{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"SizeGroupRef"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"overview","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This is typically useful when you want a column of widgets to have the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"same size, but you can’t use a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GtkGrid"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In detail, the size requested for each widget in a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GtkSizeGroup"},{"type":"text","text":" is"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the maximum of the sizes that would have been requested for each"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"widget in the size group if they were not in the size group. The mode"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"of the size group (see [method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gtk.SizeGroup.set_mode"},{"type":"text","text":"]) determines whether"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"this applies to the horizontal size, the vertical size, or both sizes."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Note that size groups only affect the amount of space requested, not"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the size that the widgets finally receive. If you want the widgets in"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GtkSizeGroup"},{"type":"text","text":" to actually be the same size, you need to pack them in"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"such a way that they get the size they request and not more."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GtkSizeGroup"},{"type":"text","text":" objects are referenced by each widget in the size group,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"so once you have added all widgets to a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GtkSizeGroup"},{"type":"text","text":", you can drop"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the initial reference to the size group with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_object_unref()"},{"type":"text","text":". If the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"widgets in the size group are subsequently destroyed, then they will"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"be removed from the size group and drop their references on the size"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"group; when all widgets have been removed, the size group will be"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"freed."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Widgets can be part of multiple size groups; GTK will compute the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"horizontal size of a widget from the horizontal requisition of all"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"widgets that can be reached from the widget by a chain of size groups"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"of type "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"horizontal"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"both"},{"type":"text","text":", and the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"vertical size from the vertical requisition of all widgets that can be"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"reached from the widget by a chain of size groups of type"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"vertical"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"both"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Note that only non-contextual sizes of every widget are ever consulted"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"by size groups (since size groups have no knowledge of what size a widget"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"will be allocated in one dimension, it cannot derive how much height"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"a widget will receive for a given width). When grouping widgets that"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"trade height for width in mode "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"vertical"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"both"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the height for the minimum width will be the requested height for all"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"widgets in the group. The same is of course true when horizontally grouping"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"width for height widgets."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Widgets that trade height-for-width should set a reasonably large minimum"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"width by way of [property"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gtk\/documentation\/Gtk\/Label"},{"type":"text","text":"] for instance. Widgets with"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"static sizes as well as widgets that grow (such as ellipsizing text) need no"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"such considerations."}]},{"anchor":"GtkSizeGroup-as-GtkBuildable","level":1,"type":"heading","text":"GtkSizeGroup as GtkBuildable"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Size groups can be specified in a UI definition by placing an "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"<object>"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"element with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"class=\"GtkSizeGroup\""},{"type":"text","text":" somewhere in the UI definition. The"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"widgets that belong to the size group are specified by a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"<widgets>"},{"type":"text","text":" element"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"that may contain multiple "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"<widget>"},{"type":"text","text":" elements, one for each member of the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"size group. The ”name” attribute gives the id of the widget."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"An example of a UI definition fragment with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GtkSizeGroup"},{"type":"text","text":":"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"xml","code":["<object class=\"GtkSizeGroup\">","  <property name=\"mode\">horizontal<\/property>","  <widgets>","    <widget name=\"radio1\"\/>","    <widget name=\"radio2\"\/>","  <\/widgets>","<\/object>"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gtk\/documentation\/Gtk\/SizeGroupRef"},{"type":"text","text":" type acts as a lightweight Swift reference to an underlying "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GtkSizeGroup"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"It exposes methods that can operate on this data type through "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gtk\/documentation\/Gtk\/SizeGroupProtocol"},{"type":"text","text":" conformance."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Use "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gtk\/documentation\/Gtk\/SizeGroupRef"},{"type":"text","text":" only as an "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"unowned"},{"type":"text","text":" reference to an existing "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GtkSizeGroup"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."}]},{"style":"note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gtk\/documentation\/Gtk\/SizeGroup"},{"type":"text","text":" (instead of "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gtk\/documentation\/Gtk\/SizeGroupRef"},{"type":"text","text":") if you want to use Automatic Reference Counting for memory management of the underlying "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GtkSizeGroup"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."}]}],"type":"aside","name":"Note"}]}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"sections":[],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/gtk\/sizegroupref"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"relationshipsSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/Gtk\/documentation\/Gtk\/BuildableProtocol","doc:\/\/Gtk\/4GLib14PointerWrapperP","doc:\/\/Gtk\/10GLibObject14GWeakCapturingP","doc:\/\/Gtk\/10GLibObject0B8ProtocolP","doc:\/\/Gtk\/documentation\/Gtk\/SizeGroupProtocol"],"kind":"relationships","title":"Conforms To","type":"conformsTo"}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/Gtk\/documentation\/Gtk\/SizeGroupRef","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"abstract":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GtkSizeGroup"},{"type":"text","text":" groups widgets together so they all request the same size."}],"kind":"symbol","metadata":{"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"SizeGroupRef"}],"title":"SizeGroupRef","roleHeading":"Structure","role":"symbol","symbolKind":"struct","externalID":"s:3Gtk12SizeGroupRefV","modules":[{"name":"Gtk"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"SizeGroupRef"}]},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/Gtk\/documentation\/Gtk"]]},"topicSections":[{"title":"Initializers","identifiers":["doc:\/\/Gtk\/documentation\/Gtk\/SizeGroupRef\/init(_:)-2tydv","doc:\/\/Gtk\/documentation\/Gtk\/SizeGroupRef\/init(_:)-4r24s","doc:\/\/Gtk\/documentation\/Gtk\/SizeGroupRef\/init(_:)-5lvp8","doc:\/\/Gtk\/documentation\/Gtk\/SizeGroupRef\/init(_:)-7pvpe","doc:\/\/Gtk\/documentation\/Gtk\/SizeGroupRef\/init(_:)-8duxe","doc:\/\/Gtk\/documentation\/Gtk\/SizeGroupRef\/init(cPointer:)","doc:\/\/Gtk\/documentation\/Gtk\/SizeGroupRef\/init(constPointer:)","doc:\/\/Gtk\/documentation\/Gtk\/SizeGroupRef\/init(gconstpointer:)","doc:\/\/Gtk\/docum